Class DTrackSDK

java.lang.Object
art.DTrackSDK
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.AutoCloseable
public class DTrackSDK
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
DTrack SDK main class derived from DTrackParser.

All methods to access tracking data are located in DTrackParser.

  • Constructor Details

    • DTrackSDK

      public DTrackSDK​(int dataPort)
      Constructor, use for pure listening mode. Using this constructor, only a UDP receiver to get tracking data from the Controller will be established. Please start measurement manually.

      Remember to insert close() after SDK usage or use try-with-resources to close all sockets.

      Parameters:
      dataPort - Port number (UDP) to receive tracking data from DTrack (0 if to be chosen by SDK)

    • DTrackSDK

      public DTrackSDK​(java.net.InetAddress multicastIp, int dataPort)
      Constructor, use for multicast listening mode. Using this constructor, only a UDP receiver to get tracking data from the Controller will be established. Please start measurement manually.

      Remember to insert close() after SDK usage or use try-with-resources to close all sockets.

      Parameters:
      multicastIp - Multicast IP address to receive data from DTrack
      dataPort - Port number (UDP) to receive tracking data from DTrack (0 if to be chosen by SDK)

    • DTrackSDK

      public DTrackSDK​(java.lang.String controllerHost, int dataPort)
      Constructor, use for communicating mode. Using this constructor, a UDP receiver to get tracking data from the Controller as well as a TCP connection with the Controller will be established. Automatically starts and stops measurement.

      Remember to insert close() after SDK usage or use try-with-resources to close all sockets.

      Parameters:
      controllerHost - Hostname or IP address of Controller
      dataPort - Port number (UDP) to receive tracking data from DTrack (0 if to be chosen by SDK)

    • sendDTrack2Command

      public int sendDTrack2Command​(java.lang.String dtrack2Command)
      Send DTrack2/DTrack3 command to DTrack (TCP command interface).

      Answers like "dtrack2 ok" and "dtrack2 err .." are processed. Both cases are reflected in the return value. getLastDTrackError() and getLastDTrackErrorDescription() will return more information.

      Parameters:
      dtrack2Command - DTrack2/DTrack3 command string
      Returns:
      0  specific answer, needs to be parsed
      1  answer is "dtrack2 ok"
      2  answer is "dtrack2 err .."; refer to getLastDataError() and getLastDTrackErrorDescription()
      <0 if error occured (-1 receive timeout, -2 wrong system type, -3 command too long, -9 broken tcp connection, -10 parser error)

    • sendDTrack2Command

      public int sendDTrack2Command​(java.lang.String dtrack2Command, java.lang.StringBuilder dtrack2Response)
      Send DTrack2/DTrack3 command to DTrack and receive answer (TCP command interface).

      Answers like "dtrack2 ok" and "dtrack2 err .." are processed. Both cases are reflected in the return value. getLastDTrackError() and getLastDTrackErrorDescription() will return more information.

      Parameters:
      dtrack2Command - DTrack2/DTrack3 command string
      dtrack2Response - DTrack2/DTrack3 answer string
      Returns:
      0  specific answer, needs to be parsed
      1  answer is "dtrack2 ok"
      2  answer is "dtrack2 err .."; refer to getLastDataError() and getLastDTrackErrorDescription()
      <0 if error occured (-1 receive timeout, -2 wrong system type, -3 command too long, -9 broken tcp connection, -10 parser error)
